Alexander Macaloney — 2:38 PM
Motor Troubleshooting:
Near the end of the first day of project development we encountered an issue wherein the motors suddenly refused to spin. We began  troubleshooting this problem by checking the physical wiring connections. This yielded no solution and the wiring appeared intact. We then utilized the multimeter to check the voltage reaching the motor drivers and the voltage leaving the motor driver. We found a mysterious 1.4 volt drop between the power entering the driver and the power going to dc motors. 
Further research allowed us to discover that this voltage drop was not an anomaly but simply normal operation of the dc motor drivers. The next day, we decided to rewire the entire vehicle from scratch. This allowed us to get three motors operational. We then identified a loose wire from ENB pin in one of the motor drivers. Correcting this bad connection allowed the fourth motor to start functioning again.
